Cheryl MoigSEVERAL dogs have, over the past few weeks, been poisoned in and around Muden. Anyone with information is requested to inform the Muden police. A case has been opened and the police are anxious to obtain any information which will be treated as confidential.In previous incidents warnings have been issued that the poisoner is a potential murderer young children will pick up anything and put it in their mouth. So please, as a matter of urgency, report any information to the Muden SAPS on 033 496 1662 or Ops 911 on 033 417 2911.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.